// A producer block whose `yield` is nested inside a loop
// (`{ for (0..5) |i| { yield i } }`) must still be recognized as an Int stage
// so its values are framed (each yielded value a distinct typed-queue entry),
// not concatenated into one byte blob. The downstream filter squares each
// value: framed -> 0,1,4,9,16 ("014916"); the old byte path concatenated
// "01234" and parsed it as a single 1234, squaring once to 1522756.
fn Int square() Int {
    for (&0) |in| {
        yield in * in
    }
}

{ for (0..5) |i| { yield i } } | square
